##On the first day of the New Year, I took 100,000 masks to Wuhan

Micro-signal Yeguangbeifukan

Function introduction the supplement of Xinmin Evening News, founded on May 1,1946, is the oldest comprehensive supplement of Chinese newspapers.

###As one of the first drivers to deliver aid to Wuhan, I feel honored; as a veteran, I have a responsibility and an obligation to help others. Wuhan Back, fear, some; regret, no!

###

###I am a 49-year-old veteran and driver of Zhongtong Express in Ningguo, China. After more than 10 years of driving trucks, traveling through many cities, pulling various kinds of goods, this is my first time to come to Wuhan, the first delivery of relief supplies. Before I left, I felt that the epidemic was far away from me. After I arrived in Wuhan, I found that the epidemic was so close to me.

###New Year's Day at 12:00 noon, I was at home and Family Dinner, the company manager called, asked me to send a batch of supplies to Wuhan. I feel very abrupt, ask manager: Send what? "relief supplies, 100,000 masks. ".

###It's okay. It's just one trip. I'll get back to him.

###After lunch, I told my family that I would go away for a long trip and deliver some important goods. I would be back the next day. After hearing this, my wife packed me some fruit, snacks and instant noodles. "COME BACK SOON! " She told me.

###At the office, I checked the car, picked up the co-pilot, and headed to the country warehouse. The warehouse was full, and the place was filled with boxes of masks. Two Stevedores in masks loaded 100,000 pairs into the van. I asked for a few masks, put one on myself, and shoved the rest into the dashboard. After loading the goods, the warehouse people gave me half a pack of cigarettes, said I was quite bold, also dare to drive to Wuhan. "No big deal, just protect yourself, " I said.

###At 6 pm, we took the highway from Ningguo and headed for Wuhan. Navigation shows that the nearest highway from Ningguo to Wuhan is the Shanghai-chongqing Expressway, covering more than 600 kilometers. It is expected to take eight hours to reach Wuhan. Walking on the road, I thought it over and over again, or to call his wife, confessed the purpose of the transport is Wuhan, my wife told me, you are the pillar of the family, to protect themselves.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
###At 4 a.m. on the second day of the Lunar New Year, we finally arrived in Wuhan. At the intersection of the highway, the police stopped us. Knowing that we were taking relief supplies to the hospital, they issued a pass and let us into the city. Unfamiliar With the Road Conditions, the co-pilot also asked the police if the car could be on the main road. After receiving a positive answer, we drove straight to the main city.

###At this time the Wuhan Urban area is basically no one, occasionally a few supermarkets with lights on, a few sporadically saw a few wearing masks of sanitation workers in cleaning the ground. I really feel like this outbreak is so close to me.

###Unfamiliar With the road, we got lost. At a traffic light, we ran into a small car. I asked the owner for directions to the health department. He was wearing a mask and gave us a thumbs-up.

###At 5 a.m. , we arrived at our destination and helped the crew remove the masks from the car. The supplies were unloaded quickly, and when a truckload of masks had been unloaded, I was relieved that, in normal circumstances, it would have been a routine delivery job, because the outbreak had made the shipment so special.

###On the way home, several relatives and friends called me to ask if the situation in Wuhan was as serious as they said on TV. I said it was no big deal. Someone from the village sent a message, telling me not to go home until the outbreak is under control.

###Zhongtong drivers Wang Shencai (left) , Xiong chuying

###They are indeed right to worry, to Wuhan delivery is a party in difficulty eight sides support, back home, I self-isolation, for the villagers to consider. When the government learned that I had brought relief supplies home from Wuhan, they also arranged for staff to take my temperature and monitor my health every day.

###As one of the first drivers to deliver relief supplies to Wuhan, I felt honored. Some people said I shouldn't go, and I understood them. As a veteran, I have the responsibility and obligation to help others, back from Wuhan, I was a little scared, but I do not regret.
